def: Of or pertaining to that division of the Celtic languages,which includes the Irish, Gaelic, and Manx. J. Peile.
An instrument similar to a mariner's compass, but withoutmagnetic needles, and having two sight vanes by which bearings aretaken, esp. such as cannot be taken by the compass.
Lady; a lady; -- a title formerly given to noble ladies whoheld a barony in their own right. Burrill.
One of a fabulous race of dwarfs who waged war with the cranes,and were destroyed.
Not dying; imperishable; unending; immortal; as, the undyingsouls of men.
A fire kindled in a public place in token of joy; a bonfire; afiring of guns in token of joy.
Pertaining to an epitaph; epitaphian.-- n.
